    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "",
      "subsections": {
        "Acute_phase": {
          "text": "Romañas sign\nswelling of the eye thought to be secondary to rubbing the feces into the eye\nChagoma\nLocalized swelling at the area of parasite entry\nNon-specific signs and symptoms\nFever\n,\nfatigue\n,\nmyalgia\n,\nheadache\n, anorexia,\nvomiting\n,\ndiarrhea\nSerious complications\nMyocarditis\n,\narrhythmia\n,\nencephalitis",
          "tables": []
        },
        "Chronic_phase": {
          "text": "Between 20-40% of patients will develop chronic complications\nCardiac complications\nDilated cardiomyopathy\n(\nCHF\n)\nDysrhythmias\nGI complications\nMegaesophagus\nMegacolon\nAchalasia\nVolvulus\nHepatosplenomegaly\n(secondary to HF)\nNeuro symptoms\nNeuritis",
          "tables": []
        }
      },
